description: From New Latin crēnātus, probably Latinization of Middle French crené, past participle of crener (“to mark with a notch”), derivative of cren, cran (“notch”).

adjectives.description: crenate (comparative more crenate, superlative most crenate)

entries.meaning: (botany) Having round or blunt teeth on its margin; scalloped.
(chemistry) Any salt or ester of crenic acid
